The power utility had promised to work towards limiting load shedding this weekend after two days of power cuts. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom  confirmed on Friday that stage 1 load shedding would be implemented on Saturday from 9am until 11pm. • How to check your load shedding schedule The power utility had promised to work towards limiting load shedding this weekend after three days of power cuts. It’s cited problems at the Medupi power station as reasons for the latest outages. Eskom spokesperson Dikatso Mothae said load shedding on Saturday was unavoidable and people should take precautions. “We will continue to double our efforts in terms of working around the clock to ensure that going forward that we don’t need to load shed,” Mothae said.